<!-- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- -->
<!-- flex: 1: -->
When applied to a flex item, flex: 1; means that the item will grow and take up all available space along the main axis within the flex container.When the screen size changes or when dealing with different screen resolutions, using flex: 1; ensures that flex items adjust dynamically.
<!-- To create grid -->::display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
gap: 10px;
<!-- Header -->:  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  <!--  z-index: 4; -->it is used in header,it determines the stacking order, which means this header will be stacked above elements with lower z-index values.










